3) QuPath: load annotations (GeoJSON) & export (if you annotate in QuPath)

If you already have GeoJSON from pathologists, skip to Step 4.

If you want to annotate in QuPath:

  1. Open QuPath → Project → Create Project → drag your WSI (.svs) into the project.

  2. Use Annotations tool to draw polygons. Create classes (e.g., Tumor, Benign).

  3. To import existing GeoJSON: File → Import → Objects from file… (select your .geojson).

    • Map properties to classes if needed (QuPath will prompt).

  4. To export your annotations: Annotations panel → select → Annotations → Export annotations → GeoJSON (per slide).

    • Save into data/annotations/SLIDE_ID.geojson.

  5. Make sure the image coordinates in GeoJSON are in full-res space (QuPath usually handles this; don’t export downsampled pixel coords unless you’ll apply the same scale later).

4) Preprocess slide-level labels (simplify “Gleason Score 5+3” → “5+3”)

slide_label_processing.py:

python
# scripts/slide_label_processing.py
import pandas as pd
import re
from pathlib import Path

CSV_FILE = Path("data/labels/slide_label_PRAD_label_edited.csv")
OUT_FILE = CSV_FILE.with_name("slide_label_PRAD_label_simple.csv")

df = pd.read_csv(CSV_FILE)

def simplify(lbl: str):
    if pd.isna(lbl):
        return lbl
    # examples: "Gleason Score 5+3 (Primary 5, Secondary 3)" -> "5+3"
    m = re.search(r'(\d)\s*\+\s*(\d)', str(lbl))
    if m:
        return f"{m.group(1)}+{m.group(2)}"
    # fallback: strip "Gleason Score" prefix if present
    lbl2 = re.sub(r'(?i)gleason\s*score\s*', '', str(lbl)).strip()
    return lbl2

df["label_simple"] = df["label"].map(simplify)  # adjust col name if needed
df.to_csv(OUT_FILE, index=False)
print("Saved:", OUT_FILE)

Run:

bash
python scripts/slide_label_processing.py

6) CLAM: extract patches

CLAM has scripts for tile/patch extraction. Common params:

  • Patch size: 256 or 512

  • Step/overlap: e.g., 256 step (no overlap) or 128 step (50% overlap)

  • Tissue mask filtering to ignore background

bash
# From project root
python clam/create_patches_fp.py \
  --source data/slides \
  --save_dir data/patches \
  --patch_size 256 \
  --seg --patch --stitch \
  --seg_level 0 --patch_level 0 \
  --step_size 256 \
  --preserve_coordinates

Outputs per slide: patch images and coordinates (CSV). CLAM will also produce stitched thumbnails useful for QA.

7) CLAM: extract patch features / embeddings

Use CLAM’s feature extraction script (default: ResNet50 pretrained on ImageNet).

bash
python clam/extract_features_fp.py \
  --data_h5_dir data/patches \
  --csv_path data/labels/slide_label_PRAD_label_simple.csv \
  --feat_dir data/features \
  --batch_size 256 \
  --target_patch_size 224

This writes per-slide .h5 feature files (one row per patch).

8) UMAP visualization of patch embeddings (notebook)

notebooks/feature_extraction.ipynb (UMAP on concatenated features; color by slide or label):

python
import h5py, numpy as np, pandas as pd, umap
from pathlib import Path
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

feat_dir = Path("../data/features")
label_df = pd.read_csv("../data/labels/slide_label_PRAD_label_simple.csv")  # columns: slide_id, label_simple

Xs, Ys, slide_ids = [], [], []
for h5p in feat_dir.glob("*.h5"):
    with h5py.File(h5p, "r") as f:
        X = f["features"][:]   # (num_patches, D)
        coords = f["coords"][:]  # (num_patches, 2)
    sid = h5p.stem
    lbl = label_df.loc[label_df["slide_id"]==sid, "label_simple"].values
    lbl = lbl[0] if len(lbl)>0 else "NA"
    Xs.append(X); slide_ids += [lbl]*len(X)

X = np.vstack(Xs)
reducer = umap.UMAP(n_neighbors=15, min_dist=0.1, metric="cosine", random_state=0)
U = reducer.fit_transform(X)

plt.figure(figsize=(7,6))
plt.scatter(U[:,0], U[:,1], s=1, alpha=0.5)
plt.title("UMAP of Patch Embeddings")
plt.axis("off")

If it’s huge, sample ~50k patches first.

9) Train CLAM with slide-level labels (MIL)

First, build a cohort split file (train/val/test):

bash
# Create splits (stratified if possible)
python clam/create_splits.py \
  --csv_path data/labels/slide_label_PRAD_label_simple.csv \
  --label_col label_simple \
  --k 5 --seed 1 --task_name PRAD_gleason

Train CLAM (single-branch, multi-class; adjust args to binary if needed):

bash
python clam/main.py \
  --task_type multi_class \
  --drop_out --early_stopping \
  --lr 2e-4 --reg 1e-5 --bag_loss ce \
  --weighted_sample \
  --k 5 --fold 0 \
  --feat_dir data/features \
  --label_csv data/labels/slide_label_PRAD_label_simple.csv \
  --save_exp_path runs/PRAD_gleason_clam_sb \
  --model_type clam_sb \
  --max_epochs 50 \
  --bag_size 200

Outputs: checkpoints, CSV logs, and attention scores per slide.

10) Visualize attention heatmaps & compare with polygons

CLAM can export attention scores per patch. You can map attention back to slide coordinates and create heatmaps.

python
# Example pseudo-code after training, to build a heatmap
import numpy as np, pandas as pd, h5py
from PIL import Image
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

slide_id = "TCGA-XX-XXXX"
feat_h5 = f"data/features/{slide_id}.h5"
attn_csv = f"runs/PRAD_gleason_clam_sb/attentions/{slide_id}.csv"  # adjust to your output path

with h5py.File(feat_h5, "r") as f:
    coords = f["coords"][:]   # (N, 2), patch (x,y) in level-0 pixels
attn = pd.read_csv(attn_csv)["attention"].values  # (N,)

# Rasterize attention into a canvas
W, H = 20000, 20000  # set to slide width/height or use bounding box
canvas = np.zeros((H//256+1, W//256+1), dtype=np.float32)
for (x,y), a in zip(coords, attn):
    canvas[y//256, x//256] = max(canvas[y//256, x//256], a)

plt.imshow(canvas, cmap="hot"); plt.title(slide_id); plt.axis("off"); plt.show()

Compare with pathologist polygons:

  • Option A: Load polygons (GeoJSON) and draw outlines on the heatmap (use shapely + matplotlib).

  • Option B: In QuPath, import your heatmap tiles as an overlay (export tile pyramid) or import attention “detections” as points with score metadata.

Common pitfalls & fixes

  • OpenSlide fails to read SVS: install openslide and python-openslide via conda-forge (done above). If still failing, the SVS may be JPEG2000: install libopenjp2 (conda-forge handles this).

  • Coordinate mismatches: ensure patch coordinates are level-0 (full-resolution) and your GeoJSON is also in level-0 pixels. If QuPath exported scaled coords, multiply by the downsample factor when overlaying.

  • Memory with UMAP: sample patches first (e.g., 50k) or do slide-wise UMAPs and then concatenate.

  • Class imbalance (e.g., rare Gleason combos): use --weighted_sample in CLAM and macro-F1 for evaluation; consider grouping labels (e.g., ≤6, 7, ≥8) if needed for baseline.

TL;DR flow you can follow literally

  1. Conda env (Step 1)

  2. Put slides in data/slides/ and annotations in data/annotations/

  3. Quick look in 01_quick_look.ipynb

  4. QuPath: import/annotate; export GeoJSON (Step 3)

  5. Simplify labels: python scripts/slide_label_processing.py

  6. Visualize all: python scripts/visualize_all.py

  7. CLAM patches: create_patches_fp.py ...

  8. CLAM features: extract_features_fp.py ...

  9. UMAP: run feature_extraction.ipynb cells

  10. Train CLAM: create_splits.py → main.py

  11. Attention heatmaps: map back to coords; overlay with polygons

  12. Marimo/ActiveVis: marimo run tile_representation_umap.py

超级清楚：你要做路线 B（WSI + 自己在 QuPath 画多边形），目的就是会“标”—完全可行，而且不需要特别专业的标注。下面给你最省事的三种用法 + 一步步怎么做 + 可直接跑的最小脚本（你只要把路径改成你的即可）。

你可以怎么用标注（3 种策略）

S1. 纯弱监督（CLAM 标准用法，最省事）

  • 你只需要一个 slide_label_simple.csv（每张切片 1 个标签，比如 tumor / benign 或 5+3）。

  • 你在 QuPath 画的多边形 不参与训练，只是用于可视化对比（最后把 CLAM 的注意力热图和你的多边形叠加）。

  • 适合你现在“随便标几块”做展示。

S2. ROI 限定弱监督（常见扩展）

  • 仍然是按切片级标签训练 CLAM，但只从你标注的 ROI 内抽 patch（减少背景干扰）。

  • 你的多边形用于挑选/过滤要喂给 CLAM 的 patch（训练时信噪比更高）。

S3. 生成“伪”patch 级标签（做个 baseline）

  • 根据多边形把 patch 标成 1/0，训练一个普通 CNN patch 分类器（不是 MIL）。

  • 和 S1 的 CLAM 弱监督结果对比，可做 sanity check/可视化演示。

结论：最推荐 S1 + 可选 S2。你就随便标几块 ROI，S1 能跑全流程；若你想更“干净”，加 S2 只在 ROI 内取 patch。

全流程（一步步照做）

Step 0. 准备目录

bash
proj/
├─ data/
│  ├─ slides/                # WSI：*.svs / *.tif
│  ├─ annotations/           # 你的 GeoJSON（每张切片 1 个）
│  └─ labels/slide_label_PRAD_label_simple.csv
├─ scripts/
│  ├─ roi_to_mask.py
│  ├─ filter_patches_by_roi.py
│  └─ attn_to_geojson.py
└─ clam/                     # CLAM 仓库

Step 1. QuPath 标注（你已经会了）

  1. QuPath 打开 WSI → 画多边形（类名随意，如 Tumor / Other）。

  2. File → Import objects from file… 可把已有 GeoJSON 导入；

  3. 导出：Annotations → Export → GeoJSON 到 data/annotations/SLIDEID.geojson。

    • 多张切片就导出多个同名 .geojson（和 slide 同 ID）。

Step 2. 准备切片级标签 slide_label_PRAD_label_simple.csv

最简单格式（两列就够）：

python-repl
slide_id,label_simple
TCGA-XX-0001,5+3
TCGA-XX-0002,benign
...

（你真没有临床标签也行，就做一个二分类：有无你画的肿瘤 ROI；或者统一给“tumor”/“benign”。）

Step 3. 用 CLAM 抽 patch

先正常把整张切片抽 patch（S1）：

bash
python clam/create_patches_fp.py \
  --source data/slides \
  --save_dir data/patches \
  --patch_size 256 \
  --seg --patch --stitch \
  --seg_level 0 --patch_level 0 \
  --step_size 256 \
  --preserve_coordinates

想做 S2（只抽 ROI 内 patch）？先按上面命令抽全量，再用下面 filter_patches_by_roi.py 把坐标过滤（或改动 CLAM 脚本源码按 mask 抽取，下面提供的过滤法最简单）。

Step 4. 提特征（ResNet50）

bash
python clam/extract_features_fp.py \
  --data_h5_dir data/patches \
  --csv_path data/labels/slide_label_PRAD_label_simple.csv \
  --feat_dir data/features \
  --batch_size 256 \
  --target_patch_size 224

Step 5. 训练 CLAM（弱监督 MIL）

bash
python clam/create_splits.py \
  --csv_path data/labels/slide_label_PRAD_label_simple.csv \
  --label_col label_simple \
  --k 5 --seed 1 --task_name PRAD_demo

python clam/main.py \
  --task_type multi_class \
  --drop_out --early_stopping \
  --lr 2e-4 --reg 1e-5 --bag_loss ce --weighted_sample \
  --k 5 --fold 0 \
  --feat_dir data/features \
  --label_csv data/labels/slide_label_PRAD_label_simple.csv \
  --save_exp_path runs/PRAD_demo_clam_sb \
  --model_type clam_sb \
  --max_epochs 30

Step 6. 导出注意力 → 回 QuPath 可视化

训练完成后会有每张切片的 patch 注意力分数。把这些分数变成 GeoJSON Points（QuPath 可导入）或生成热图图片叠加。下面给你最小可运行脚本。

关键脚本（可直接用）

A) 把 GeoJSON 多边形变成 mask（S2/S3 用）

scripts/roi_to_mask.py

python
import json, numpy as np
from PIL import Image, ImageDraw
from shapely.geometry import shape
from pathlib import Path

# 输入
geojson_path = Path("data/annotations/TCGA-XX-0001.geojson")
# 你需要知道切片 level-0 的宽高（用 openslide 读一下即可；这里先手填）
W, H = 100000, 80000

data = json.load(open(geojson_path))
canvas = Image.new("L", (W, H), 0)
draw = ImageDraw.Draw(canvas)

for feat in data["features"]:
    geom = shape(feat["geometry"])  # 多边形
    if geom.geom_type == "Polygon":
        pts = [(x, y) for x, y in np.array(geom.exterior.coords)]
        draw.polygon(pts, outline=1, fill=1)
    elif geom.geom_type == "MultiPolygon":
        for poly in geom.geoms:
            pts = [(x, y) for x, y in np.array(poly.exterior.coords)]
            draw.polygon(pts, outline=1, fill=1)

canvas.save("data/annotations/TCGA-XX-0001_mask.png")  # 1=ROI, 0=背景
print("Saved mask.")

提示：用 openslide.OpenSlide(path).dimensions 得到 (W,H)；或你只画了一小块，可以用 bounding box 裁剪以减小尺寸。

B) 过滤 patch（只保留落在 ROI 里的 patch）

scripts/filter_patches_by_roi.py

python
import h5py, numpy as np
from PIL import Image
from pathlib import Path

slide_id = "TCGA-XX-0001"
feat_h5_in  = Path(f"data/patches/{slide_id}.h5")      # create_patches 输出
feat_h5_out = Path(f"data/patches/{slide_id}_roi.h5")
mask_img = Image.open(f"data/annotations/{slide_id}_mask.png").convert("L")
mask = np.array(mask_img) > 0

with h5py.File(feat_h5_in, "r") as fin, h5py.File(feat_h5_out, "w") as fout:
    coords = fin["coords"][:]          # (N,2) level-0像素坐标 (x,y)
    for k in fin.keys():
        if k == "coords": continue
        fout.create_dataset(k, data=fin[k][:])
    keep = []
    for i,(x,y) in enumerate(coords):
        # 按你的 patch_size 步长决定采样点，这里用 patch 左上角判断
        if 0 <= y < mask.shape[0] and 0 <= x < mask.shape[1] and mask[int(y), int(x)]:
            keep.append(i)
    keep = np.array(keep, dtype=np.int64)
    fout.create_dataset("coords", data=coords[keep])
print("Filtered to ROI patches.")

然后把 extract_features_fp.py 的 --data_h5_dir 指向你 _roi.h5 的目录即可（或把原文件替换）。

C) 把注意力导出为 GeoJSON（QuPath 可导入）

scripts/attn_to_geojson.py

python
import json, pandas as pd, h5py
from pathlib import Path

slide_id = "TCGA-XX-0001"
# 训练输出里的注意力（路径按你的 runs 目录为准）
attn_csv = Path(f"runs/PRAD_demo_clam_sb/attentions/{slide_id}.csv")
patch_h5 = Path(f"data/features/{slide_id}.h5")  # 或者你的 _roi.h5

attn = pd.read_csv(attn_csv)["attention"].values
with h5py.File(patch_h5, "r") as f:
    coords = f["coords"][:]   # (N,2) (x,y)

# 归一化到 [0,1]
a = (attn - attn.min()) / (attn.ptp() + 1e-8)

features = []
for (x,y), s in zip(coords, a):
    features.append({
        "type": "Feature",
        "properties": {"attention": float(s)},
        "geometry": {"type": "Point", "coordinates": [float(x), float(y)]}
    })

geo = {"type": "FeatureCollection", "features": features}
out = Path(f"runs/PRAD_demo_clam_sb/attn_geojson/{slide_id}_attn.geojson")
out.parent.mkdir(parents=True, exist_ok=True)
json.dump(geo, open(out, "w"))
print("Saved:", out)

在 QuPath 中：File → Import objects from file... 选择这个 _attn.geojson，即可看到一堆点。你可以按 attention 设色阶（Measurement heatmap），或把高分点做成伪热图。

  4. 对比（可选）：S1（全量抽 patch） vs S2（只 ROI 内 patch），以及简单 CNN 的 S3 基线各一张图。

完全可以做到，你有两种标注“粒度”，对应两条可行流水线：

TL;DR（先说结论）

  • CLAM（弱监督 MIL）需要的是“按切片的 CSV 标签”：一行一个切片（slide），而不是每个 patch 都手动标。

  • 你画 ROI 有两种用法：

    1. 只用于可视化/过滤：依然只给切片级标签给 CLAM（最省事）。

    2. 把 ROI 转成 patch 级伪标签：用“点在多边形内=阳性”的规则自动给 patch 打标签，做一个 patch-CNN baseline 或做数据清洗，也可以再聚合成切片级标签。

你提到的“先让 CLAM 切 patch → 回 QuPath 手动标几个 → 再补全其余 → 导回 QuPath”也能做，下面给你两套从易到难的具体步骤与脚本骨架。

路线 A（推荐，最省力）：切片级 CSV + CLAM（ROI 只做过滤/对比）

  1. 在 QuPath 画少量 ROI（Tumor/Benign 等），导出到 data/annotations/SLIDEID.geojson。

  2. 做切片级 CSV（CLAM 用）。三种生成方式任选：

    • 手工做一个 slide_label_PRAD_label_simple.csv（两列就够）

      slide_id,label_simple
TCGA-XX-0001,tumor
TCGA-XX-0002,benign

    • 如果没有临床标签，可用**“是否存在肿瘤 ROI”** 自动生成（下面有脚本骨架）。

    • 如果有 Gleason 文本标签，先简化成“5+3”等，再喂给 CLAM。

  3. 抽 patch（CLAM 自带）

    bash
    python clam/create_patches_fp.py --source data/slides --save_dir data/patches \
  --patch_size 256 --seg --patch --stitch --seg_level 0 --patch_level 0 \
  --step_size 256 --preserve_coordinates

    想降低噪声，可只保留 ROI 内 patch（下面给过滤脚本骨架）。

  4. 提特征 → 训练 CLAM（用上面的 CSV）。

  5. 导出注意力 → 回 QuPath 导入（points GeoJSON），做“模型关注 vs 你画的 ROI”的对比可视化。

生成“是否有肿瘤 ROI”的切片 CSV（脚本骨架）

python
# make_slide_csv_from_roi.py
# 读取每张 slide 的 GeoJSON，如果存在 class=="Tumor" 的多边形，就标 tumor，否则 benign
import json, pandas as pd
from pathlib import Path

ann_dir = Path("data/annotations")
rows = []
for g in sorted(ann_dir.glob("*.geojson")):
    dat = json.load(open(g))
    has_tumor = False
    for f in dat["features"]:
        cls = (f.get("properties") or {}).get("classification", "") or (f.get("properties") or {}).get("name","")
        if str(cls).lower() in ["tumor","cancer","malignant"]:
            has_tumor = True; break
    rows.append({"slide_id": g.stem, "label_simple": "tumor" if has_tumor else "benign"})

pd.DataFrame(rows).to_csv("data/labels/slide_label_PRAD_label_simple.csv", index=False)
print("Saved data/labels/slide_label_PRAD_label_simple.csv")

路线 B（你提出的：切 patch → 回 QuPath少量标 → 机器补全 → 再导回）

这个更“互动”，适合演示你“会标注”的能力。

步骤概览

  1. CLAM 切 patch（同上）。

  2. 把 patch 坐标导成 GeoJSON 点，导入 QuPath（点对象可以被你快速赋类）。

  3. 在 QuPath 只标少量 patch 点（例如 100–300 个点，设成 Tumor/Benign）。导出 GeoJSON。

  4. 把你标的那一小撮点匹配回 patch 列表 → 得到一个 patch_level.csv（有 label 的少量 patch）。

  5. 用已标 patch 训练一个轻量 patch-CNN 或者做最近邻/ROI 规则的“伪标签补全”（pseudo-labeling），给剩余 patch 自动打标签。

  6. （可选）把补全后的 patch 标签多数投票成切片级 → 得到 slide_label_PRAD_label_simple.csv，再喂给 CLAM 做弱监督；或直接用 patch-CNN 做 patch 分类任务。

  7. 导回 QuPath：把（注意力/补全标签）变成 GeoJSON Points 导入，做最终可视化。

关键脚本骨架

(1) 从 CLAM 的 patch 坐标生成 QuPath 可导入的点：

import h5py, json
from pathlib import Path

h5_path = Path("data/patches/TCGA-XX-0001.h5")
pts = []
with h5py.File(h5_path, "r") as f:
    coords = f["coords"][:]  # (N,2) level-0像素坐标 (x,y)
for i,(x,y) in enumerate(coords):

(2) 把你在 QuPath 标好的点合并回 patch 列表：

# geojson_points_to_patch_csv.py
import json, pandas as pd
from pathlib import Path

labeled_geojson = Path("data/annotations/TCGA-XX-0001_patches_labeled.geojson")
dat = json.load(open(labeled_geojson))
rows = []
for f in dat["features"]:

(3) 伪标签补全（两种简单法）

  • 多边形填充法（最稳）：直接用你的 ROI 多边形，点在肿瘤多边形内→tumor，否则→benign，一键给所有 patch 标上（这是你说的“少量标注→补全”的最简单版本，效果通常不错）：

python
# propagate_labels_by_polygon.py
import json, h5py, numpy as np, pandas as pd
from shapely.geometry import shape, Point
from pathlib import Path

slide_id = "TCGA-XX-0001"
h5p = Path(f"data/patches/{slide_id}.h5")
ann = json.load(open(f"data/annotations/{slide_id}.geojson"))

tumor_polys = []
for f in ann["features"]:
    cls = (f.get("properties") or {}).get("classification","").lower()
    if "tumor" in cls or "cancer" in cls or "malignant" in cls:
        tumor_polys.append(shape(f["geometry"]))

with h5py.File(h5p, "r") as f:
    coords = f["coords"][:]  # (N,2)

def in_tumor(x,y):
    p = Point(float(x), float(y))
    return any(poly.contains(p) for poly in tumor_polys)

rows=[]
for i,(x,y) in enumerate(coords):
    lbl = "tumor" if in_tumor(x,y) else "benign"
    rows.append({"slide_id": slide_id, "patch_id": i, "label": lbl})
pd.DataFrame(rows).to_csv(f"data/labels/{slide_id}_patch_pseudo.csv", index=False)
print("Saved patch pseudo labels.")

  • 半监督/最近邻传播：用你手标的少数 patch 训练一个轻量 CNN 或做 kNN，把标签传播给其余 patch（需要再写训练/特征提取代码，时间更久，这里不展开）。

(4) 可选：把 patch 标签聚合成切片级 CSV（给 CLAM 或对比）

python
# patch_to_slide_majority.py
import pandas as pd
from pathlib import Path

df = pd.read_csv("data/labels/TCGA-XX-0001_patch_pseudo.csv")  # 或合并多张
slide = df.groupby("slide_id")["label"].apply(lambda s: s.value_counts().idxmax()).reset_index()
slide.columns = ["slide_id","label_simple"]
slide.to_csv("data/labels/slide_label_from_patch.csv", index=False)

第 2 步｜把 ROI 多边形转成像素级 mask（自动读取切片尺寸）

把下面脚本保存为 scripts/roi_to_mask.py，不用手填宽高，它会通过 OpenSlide 自动读。

python
# scripts/roi_to_mask.py
import json, numpy as np
from pathlib import Path
from PIL import Image, ImageDraw
import openslide
from shapely.geometry import shape

ann_dir = Path("data/annotations")
slide_dir = Path("data/slides")
out_dir = ann_dir  # 输出到同目录

for gj in sorted(ann_dir.glob("*.geojson")):
    slide_id = gj.stem
    # 找到对应的 svs/tif
    slide_path = None
    for ext in (".svs", ".tif", ".ndpi"):
        p = slide_dir / f"{slide_id}{ext}"
        if p.exists():
            slide_path = p; break
    assert slide_path is not None, f"Slide file not found for {slide_id}"

    # 读切片尺寸（level-0）
    wsi = openslide.OpenSlide(str(slide_path))
    W, H = wsi.dimensions  # (width, height)

    # 读 GeoJSON
    data = json.load(open(gj))
    canvas = Image.new("L", (W, H), 0)
    draw = ImageDraw.Draw(canvas)

    for feat in data["features"]:
        geom = shape(feat["geometry"])
        if geom.geom_type == "Polygon":
            pts = [(x, y) for x, y in np.asarray(geom.exterior.coords)]
            draw.polygon(pts, outline=1, fill=1)
        elif geom.geom_type == "MultiPolygon":
            for poly in geom.geoms:
                pts = [(x, y) for x, y in np.asarray(poly.exterior.coords)]
                draw.polygon(pts, outline=1, fill=1)

    out_path = out_dir / f"{slide_id}_mask.png"
    canvas.save(out_path)
    print("Saved:", out_path)

第 4 步（可选但强烈建议）｜只保留 ROI 内的 patch

把下面脚本保存为 scripts/filter_patches_by_roi.py：

python
# scripts/filter_patches_by_roi.py
import h5py, numpy as np
from pathlib import Path
from PIL import Image

patch_h5 = Path("data/patches/CMU-2.h5")              # 输入
mask_png = Path("data/annotations/CMU-2_mask.png")    # 第2步生成
out_h5   = Path("data/patches/CMU-2_roi.h5")          # 输出

mask = np.array(Image.open(mask_png).convert("L")) > 0

with h5py.File(patch_h5, "r") as fin, h5py.File(out_h5, "w") as fout:
    coords = fin["coords"][:]    # (N,2) (x,y) level-0
    keep_idx = []
    for i,(x,y) in enumerate(coords):
        x=int(x); y=int(y)
        if 0 <= x < mask.shape[1] and 0 <= y < mask.shape[0] and mask[y,x]:
            keep_idx.append(i)
    keep_idx = np.array(keep_idx, dtype=np.int64)

    # 复制数据集，只保留 keep
    for k in fin.keys():
        if k == "coords": continue
        data = fin[k][:]
        if len(data)==len(coords):
            data = data[keep_idx]
        fout.create_dataset(k, data=data)
    fout.create_dataset("coords", data=coords[keep_idx])

print("Filtered patches saved to", out_h5)

保存为 scripts/attn_to_geojson.py：

python
# scripts/attn_to_geojson.py
import json, pandas as pd, h5py
from pathlib import Path

slide_id = "CMU-2"
attn_csv = Path(f"runs/demo_clam_sb/attentions/{slide_id}.csv")  # 按你的输出目录调整
feat_h5  = Path(f"data/features/{slide_id}.h5")                  # 或 _roi.h5

attn = pd.read_csv(attn_csv)["attention"].values
with h5py.File(feat_h5, "r") as f:
    coords = f["coords"][:]  # (N,2)

a = (attn - attn.min()) / (attn.ptp() + 1e-8)

features = []
for (x,y), s in zip(coords, a):
    features.append({
        "type":"Feature",
        "properties":{"attention":float(s)},
        "geometry":{"type":"Point","coordinates":[float(x), float(y)]}
    })
geo = {"type":"FeatureCollection","features":features}
out = Path(f"runs/demo_clam_sb/attn_geojson/{slide_id}_attn.geojson")
out.parent.mkdir(parents=True, exist_ok=True)
json.dump(geo, open(out,"w"))
print("Saved:", out)

你问的关键点再回答一下

  • “是不是要一个 CSV，每个切片一个标签？”
    是的，CLAM 的弱监督训练依赖切片级 CSV（每行一个 slide 的标签）。你的 ROI 主要用来过滤 patch 和做可视化对比；不需要给每个 patch 手工打标签。

  • “能把结果导回 QuPath吗？”
    当然。注意力和伪标签都可以导成 GeoJSON 点 导回 QuPath，做最终对比展示。

短答：你在 QuPath 里画的这个 ROI 不是“自动成为整张切片的标签”。它只是一个“多边形标注”。
要让 CLAM 训练，你仍然需要一个切片级 CSV 标签（每行一个 slide 的标签）。不过你画的 ROI 很有用，可以用来：

  1. 给整张切片定标签（弱监督 CLAM 用）

    • 规则：这张切片里有你标的 Tumor ROI ⇒ 这张切片的标签就是 tumor；否则 benign。

    • 生成一个 CSV：slide_id,label_simple（例如 CMU-2,tumor）。

  2. 把 ROI 当作“弱标签”，直接给 patch 打伪标签（做 patch 级分析/基线）

  3. 只做表征分析（无监督）

C. 用“嵌套 ROI”自动生成 patch 级伪标签

把下面脚本存为 scripts/label_patches_from_nested_roi.py，它会：

  • 读取 CMU-2.h5 的 patch 坐标；

  • 读取 CMU-2.geojson 的两个多边形；

  • 给每个 patch 贴上 tumor / benign / ignore 三类中的一个；

  • 输出 data/labels/CMU-2_patch_labels.csv（可直接用于训练 patch 分类器或回 QuPath 可视化）。

python
# scripts/label_patches_from_nested_roi.py
from pathlib import Path
import h5py, json, pandas as pd
from shapely.geometry import shape, Point

slide_id   = "CMU-2"
h5_path    = Path(f"data/patches/{slide_id}.h5")
geojson_fn = Path(f"data/annotations/{slide_id}.geojson")
out_csv    = Path(f"data/labels/{slide_id}_patch_labels.csv")

# 1) 载入多边形
g = json.load(open(geojson_fn))
tumor_polys = []
outer_polys = []  # ROI / Region
for f in g["features"]:
    props = (f.get("properties") or {})
    cls = (props.get("classification") or props.get("name") or "").lower()
    geom = shape(f["geometry"])
    if "tumor" in cls:
        tumor_polys.append(geom)
    else:
        outer_polys.append(geom)  # 其它都当外圈

def in_any(polys, x, y):
    p = Point(float(x), float(y))
    return any(poly.contains(p) for poly in polys)

# 2) 载入 patch 坐标并打标签
rows = []
with h5py.File(h5_path, "r") as f:
    coords = f["coords"][:]  # (N,2) (x, y)

for i, (x, y) in enumerate(coords):
    if in_any(tumor_polys, x, y):
        lab = "tumor"
    elif in_any(outer_polys, x, y):
        lab = "benign"
    else:
        lab = "ignore"
    rows.append({"slide_id": slide_id, "patch_id": i, "x": int(x), "y": int(y), "label": lab})

df = pd.DataFrame(rows)
df = df[df["label"] != "ignore"].reset_index(drop=True)  # 只保留 ROI 内两类
out_csv.parent.mkdir(parents=True, exist_ok=True)
df.to_csv(out_csv, index=False)
print("Saved:", out_csv, "counts:", df["label"].value_counts().to_dict())

import json, pandas as pd
from pathlib import Path

slide_id   = "CMU-2"
pred_csv   = Path(f"runs/patch_clf/{slide_id}_pred.csv")  # 你推理后的结果：必须含 x,y,prob_tumor

        "type":"Feature",
        "properties":{"prob_tumor": float(r.prob_tumor),

        "geometry":{"type":"Point","coordinates":[float(r.x), float(r.y)]}
    })
geo = {"type":"FeatureCollection","features":features}

python
# scripts/label_patches_from_nested_roi.py
from pathlib import Path
import h5py, json, pandas as pd
from shapely.geometry import shape, Point

slide_id   = "CMU-2"  # 改成你的
h5_path    = Path(f"data/patches/{slide_id}.h5")
geojson_fn = Path(f"data/annotations/{slide_id}.geojson")
out_csv    = Path(f"data/labels/{slide_id}_patch_labels.csv")

g = json.load(open(geojson_fn))
tumor_polys, outer_polys = [], []
for f in g["features"]:
    props = (f.get("properties") or {})
    cls = (props.get("classification") or props.get("name") or "").lower()
    geom = shape(f["geometry"])
    if "tumor" in cls:
        tumor_polys.append(geom)
    else:
        outer_polys.append(geom)  # 其它都视为外圈

def inside(polys, xy):
    p = Point(float(xy[0]), float(xy[1]))
    return any(poly.contains(p) for poly in polys)

rows = []
with h5py.File(h5_path, "r") as f:
    coords = f["coords"][:]  # (N,2) (x,y)

for i,(x,y) in enumerate(coords):
    if inside(tumor_polys, (x,y)):
        lab = "tumor"
    elif inside(outer_polys, (x,y)):
        lab = "benign"
    else:
        continue  # ROI 外忽略
    rows.append({"slide_id": slide_id, "patch_id": i, "x": int(x), "y": int(y), "label": lab})

pd.DataFrame(rows).to_csv(out_csv, index=False)
print("Saved:", out_csv)

运行：

bash
python scripts/label_patches_from_nested_roi.py

python
# scripts/patch_labels_to_geojson.py
import json, pandas as pd
from pathlib import Path

slide_id = "CMU-2"
df = pd.read_csv(f"data/labels/{slide_id}_patch_labels.csv")  # x,y,label
features = []
for r in df.itertuples():
    features.append({
        "type":"Feature",
        "properties":{"label": r.label},
        "geometry":{"type":"Point","coordinates":[float(r.x), float(r.y)]}
    })
geo = {"type":"FeatureCollection","features":features}
out = Path(f"runs/patch_labels/{slide_id}_patch_labels.geojson")
out.parent.mkdir(parents=True, exist_ok=True)
json.dump(geo, open(out,"w"))
print("Saved:", out)

// 导出当前图像中的所有 Annotation 为 GeoJSON（坐标为 Level-0 像素）

geojson_fn = Path("/Users/yhu10/Desktop/VLM/pipline_data_patch_level/path_level_projcet") / f"{slide_id}.geojson"

assert geojson_fn.exists(), f"geojson not found: {geojson_fn}"
out_csv.parent.mkdir(parents=True, exist_ok=True)

ChatGPT said:

这一步就是把整张 WSI（.svs）切成很多小块 patch，并把每个 patch 的像素坐标等信息保存下来，供后续提特征、打标签、可视化用。具体做了几件事：

  1. 组织分割（--seg）
    先做一个粗分割，找到有组织的区域（排除纯白背景），避免切出一堆空白 patch。

  2. 切块/取样（--patch）
    按你给的 --patch_size 256 和 --step_size 256 在 patch_level（这里是 0，最高分辨率）上平铺取块：

    • patch_size=256：每个小块 256×256 像素；

    • step_size=256：块与块之间不重叠；如果想 50% 重叠，就设 --step_size 128。

  3. 生成拼贴预览（--stitch）
    会产出一张拼接缩略图，方便你目测切块覆盖是不是合理。

  4. 保存坐标（--preserve_coordinates）
    把每个 patch 的level-0 像素坐标 (x, y) 存起来（很重要）：

    • 这样我们才能把 patch 和你在 QuPath 画的 ROI（GeoJSON 多边形）做空间匹配，从而自动判定“落在 Tumor 里还是 ROI 里”。

  5. 输出内容

    • data/patches/CMU-2.h5：一个 HDF5 汇总文件，常见键：

      • coords：形如 (N, 2) 的数组，记录每个 patch 的 (x, y) 位置（level-0）。

      • 还可能有 size, downsample 等元信息（依 CLAM 版本而定）。

    • data/patches/patches/CMU-2/...：实际切下来的 patch 图（可选）。

    • data/patches/masks/、stitches/：组织分割和拼贴预览图。

为什么必须做这一步？

  • 后面的 特征提取（extract_features_fp.py）就是逐 patch 读图、喂给 ResNet/ViT 得到向量；

  • 和 ROI 匹配打伪标签 要用到 coords；

  • 把预测/注意力导回 QuPath 也要靠这些坐标在原图上定位。

5) 用你的 GeoJSON 自动生成 patch 级伪标签

把下面脚本保存为：

swift
/Users/yhu10/Desktop/VLM/pipline_data_patch_level/label_patches_from_nested_roi.py

（里面的路径已经按你的目录写好了）

python
from pathlib import Path
import h5py, json, pandas as pd
from shapely.geometry import shape, Point

slide_id = "CMU-2"

h5_path = Path("/Users/yhu10/Desktop/VLM/pipline_data_patch_level/data/patches") / f"{slide_id}.h5"
geojson_fn = Path("/Users/yhu10/Desktop/VLM/pipline_data_patch_level/path_level_projcet") / f"{slide_id}.geojson"
out_csv = Path("/Users/yhu10/Desktop/VLM/pipline_data_patch_level/data/labels") / f"{slide_id}_patch_labels.csv"

assert h5_path.exists(), f"patch h5 not found: {h5_path}"
assert geojson_fn.exists(), f"geojson not found: {geojson_fn}"
out_csv.parent.mkdir(parents=True, exist_ok=True)

g = json.load(open(geojson_fn))
tumor_polys, outer_polys = [], []
for f in g["features"]:
    props = (f.get("properties") or {})
    cls = (props.get("classification") or props.get("name") or "").lower()
    geom = shape(f["geometry"])
    if "tumor" in cls:
        tumor_polys.append(geom)
    else:
        outer_polys.append(geom)  # 其余视为外圈ROI

def inside(polys, x, y):
    p = Point(float(x), float(y))
    return any(poly.contains(p) for poly in polys)

rows = []
with h5py.File(h5_path, "r") as f:
    coords = f["coords"][:]  # (N,2) (x,y) level-0

for i,(x,y) in enumerate(coords):
    if inside(tumor_polys, x, y):
        lab = "tumor"
    elif inside(outer_polys, x, y):
        lab = "benign"
    else:
        continue  # ROI外忽略
    rows.append({"slide_id": slide_id, "patch_id": i, "x": int(x), "y": int(y), "label": lab})

pd.DataFrame(rows).to_csv(out_csv, index=False)
print("Saved:", out_csv)

运行它（仍在刚才的 venv 环境里）：

bash
python /Users/yhu10/Desktop/VLM/pipline_data_patch_level/label_patches_from_nested_roi.py

    })

Yes—totally possible. You can run the CLAM patching pipeline in a single Jupyter notebook without using the CLI. Below are drop-in notebook cells that:

  • point Python to your CLAM code (so wsi_core.* imports work),

  • run seg_and_patch(...) directly (no argparse),

  • save patches/HDF5 the same way the script does.

I’ll also give you a fallback in case OpenSlide (the C library) isn’t available.

4) (Notebook cell) Paste the minimal functions (adapted for notebook)

I slightly adapted your script into notebook-friendly functions (removed argparse; same logic).

python
def stitching(file_path, wsi_object, downscale=64):
    start = time.time()
    heatmap = StitchCoords(file_path, wsi_object, downscale=downscale, bg_color=(0,0,0), alpha=-1, draw_grid=False)
    total_time = time.time() - start
    return heatmap, total_time

def segment(WSI_object, seg_params=None, filter_params=None, mask_file=None):
    start_time = time.time()
    if mask_file is not None:
        WSI_object.initSegmentation(mask_file)
    else:
        WSI_object.segmentTissue(**seg_params, filter_params=filter_params)
    seg_time_elapsed = time.time() - start_time
    return WSI_object, seg_time_elapsed

def patching(WSI_object, **kwargs):
    start_time = time.time()
    file_path = WSI_object.process_contours(**kwargs)
    patch_time_elapsed = time.time() - start_time
    return file_path, patch_time_elapsed

def seg_and_patch(source, save_dir, patch_save_dir, mask_save_dir, stitch_save_dir, 
                  patch_size=256, step_size=256, 
                  seg_params={'seg_level': -1, 'sthresh': 8, 'mthresh': 7, 'close': 4, 'use_otsu': False,
                              'keep_ids': 'none', 'exclude_ids': 'none'},
                  filter_params={'a_t':100, 'a_h': 16, 'max_n_holes':8}, 
                  vis_params={'vis_level': -1, 'line_thickness': 500},
                  patch_params={'use_padding': True, 'contour_fn': 'four_pt'},
                  patch_level=0,
                  use_default_params=False, 
                  seg=False, save_mask=True, 
                  stitch=False, 
                  patch=False, auto_skip=True, process_list=None):
    source = str(source)
    save_dir = str(save_dir)
    patch_save_dir = str(patch_save_dir)
    mask_save_dir = str(mask_save_dir)
    stitch_save_dir = str(stitch_save_dir)

    # Prepare slide list / df
    slides = sorted([s for s in os.listdir(source) if os.path.isfile(os.path.join(source, s))])
    if process_list is None:
        df = initialize_df(slides, seg_params, filter_params, vis_params, patch_params)
    else:
        df = pd.read_csv(process_list)
        df = initialize_df(df, seg_params, filter_params, vis_params, patch_params)

    mask = df['process'] == 1
    process_stack = df[mask]
    total = len(process_stack)

    legacy_support = 'a' in df.keys()
    if legacy_support:
        print('legacy segmentation csv file detected, enabling legacy support')
        df = df.assign(**{
            'a_t': np.full((len(df)), int(filter_params['a_t']), dtype=np.uint32),
            'a_h': np.full((len(df)), int(filter_params['a_h']), dtype=np.uint32),
            'max_n_holes': np.full((len(df)), int(filter_params['max_n_holes']), dtype=np.uint32),
            'line_thickness': np.full((len(df)), int(vis_params['line_thickness']), dtype=np.uint32),
            'contour_fn': np.full((len(df)), patch_params['contour_fn'])
        })

    seg_times = patch_times = stitch_times = 0.0

    for i in tqdm(range(total)):
        Path(save_dir).mkdir(parents=True, exist_ok=True)
        df.to_csv(os.path.join(save_dir, 'process_list_autogen.csv'), index=False)

        idx = process_stack.index[i]
        slide = process_stack.loc[idx, 'slide_id']
        print(f"\nProcessing {i+1}/{total}: {slide}")
        df.loc[idx, 'process'] = 0
        slide_id, _ = os.path.splitext(slide)

        if auto_skip and os.path.isfile(os.path.join(patch_save_dir, slide_id + '.h5')):
            print(f"{slide_id} already exists, skipping")
            df.loc[idx, 'status'] = 'already_exist'
            continue

        # init WSI
        full_path = os.path.join(source, slide)
        WSI_object = WholeSlideImage(full_path)

        if use_default_params:
            current_vis_params   = vis_params.copy()
            current_filter_params= filter_params.copy()
            current_seg_params   = seg_params.copy()
            current_patch_params = patch_params.copy()
        else:
            current_vis_params = {}
            current_filter_params = {}
            current_seg_params = {}
            current_patch_params = {}
            for key in vis_params.keys():
                if legacy_support and key == 'vis_level':
                    df.loc[idx, key] = -1
                current_vis_params[key] = df.loc[idx, key]
            for key in filter_params.keys():
                if legacy_support and key == 'a_t':
                    old_area = df.loc[idx, 'a']
                    seg_level = df.loc[idx, 'seg_level']
                    scale = WSI_object.level_downsamples[seg_level]
                    adjusted_area = int(old_area * (scale[0] * scale[1]) / (512*512))
                    current_filter_params[key] = adjusted_area
                    df.loc[idx, key] = adjusted_area
                current_filter_params[key] = df.loc[idx, key]
            for key in seg_params.keys():
                if legacy_support and key == 'seg_level':
                    df.loc[idx, key] = -1
                current_seg_params[key] = df.loc[idx, key]
            for key in patch_params.keys():
                current_patch_params[key] = df.loc[idx, key]

        # Auto-pick levels if <0
        if current_vis_params['vis_level'] < 0:
            if len(WSI_object.level_dim) == 1:
                current_vis_params['vis_level'] = 0
            else:
                best_level = WSI_object.getOpenSlide().get_best_level_for_downsample(64)
                current_vis_params['vis_level'] = best_level

        if current_seg_params['seg_level'] < 0:
            if len(WSI_object.level_dim) == 1:
                current_seg_params['seg_level'] = 0
            else:
                best_level = WSI_object.getOpenSlide().get_best_level_for_downsample(64)
                current_seg_params['seg_level'] = best_level

        # id lists
        keep_ids = str(current_seg_params['keep_ids'])
        current_seg_params['keep_ids'] = [] if keep_ids == 'none' or len(keep_ids)==0 else np.array(keep_ids.split(',')).astype(int)
        exclude_ids = str(current_seg_params['exclude_ids'])
        current_seg_params['exclude_ids'] = [] if exclude_ids == 'none' or len(exclude_ids)==0 else np.array(exclude_ids.split(',')).astype(int)

        # guard on huge downsample dims
        w, h = WSI_object.level_dim[current_seg_params['seg_level']]
        if w*h > 1e8:
            print(f"level_dim {w}x{h} too large for segmentation; skipping")
            df.loc[idx, 'status'] = 'failed_seg'
            continue

        df.loc[idx, 'vis_level'] = current_vis_params['vis_level']
        df.loc[idx, 'seg_level'] = current_seg_params['seg_level']

        # Run stages
        seg_time_elapsed = -1
        if seg:
            WSI_object, seg_time_elapsed = segment(WSI_object, current_seg_params, current_filter_params)

        if save_mask:
            vis = WSI_object.visWSI(**current_vis_params)
            Path(mask_save_dir).mkdir(parents=True, exist_ok=True)
            vis.save(os.path.join(mask_save_dir, slide_id + '.jpg'))

        patch_time_elapsed = -1
        if patch:
            current_patch_params.update({'patch_level': patch_level,
                                         'patch_size': patch_size,
                                         'step_size': step_size,
                                         'save_path': patch_save_dir})
            file_path, patch_time_elapsed = patching(WSI_object=WSI_object, **current_patch_params)

        stitch_time_elapsed = -1
        if stitch:
            file_path = os.path.join(patch_save_dir, slide_id + '.h5')
            if os.path.isfile(file_path):
                heatmap, stitch_time_elapsed = stitching(file_path, WSI_object, downscale=64)
                Path(stitch_save_dir).mkdir(parents=True, exist_ok=True)
                heatmap.save(os.path.join(stitch_save_dir, slide_id + '.jpg'))

        print(f"seg: {seg_time_elapsed:.2f}s | patch: {patch_time_elapsed:.2f}s | stitch: {stitch_time_elapsed:.2f}s")
        df.loc[idx, 'status'] = 'processed'
        seg_times   += max(seg_time_elapsed, 0)
        patch_times += max(patch_time_elapsed, 0)
        stitch_times+= max(stitch_time_elapsed, 0)

    n = max(total, 1)
    print("avg seg(s):", seg_times/n, "avg patch(s):", patch_times/n, "avg stitch(s):", stitch_times/n)
    df.to_csv(os.path.join(save_dir, 'process_list_autogen.csv'), index=False)
    return seg_times/n, patch_times/n

You’ve hit a NumPy 2 ↔️ OpenCV ABI mismatch:

  • Your Python has NumPy 2.0.2.

  • The wheel you installed for opencv-python-headless 4.9.0.80 was compiled against NumPy 1.x, so it crashes with ImportError: numpy.core.multiarray failed to import / _ARRAY_API not found.

You have two solid ways to fix it. I recommend the clean venv so you don’t keep fighting your system Python.

✅ Option A (recommended): make a clean venv with compatible pins

This avoids mixing packages in your system’s ~/Library/Python/3.9.

  1. Create & activate a virtual environment:

bash
python3 -m venv ~/.venvs/pathlvl
source ~/.venvs/pathlvl/bin/activate
python -V

  1. Install package versions that play nice together (NumPy 1.x stack):

# Pin numpy 1.x and compatible wheels:

  1. (For notebooks) add this venv as a Jupyter kernel:

  1. In Jupyter, switch the kernel to Python (pathlvl) and re-run your notebook cells (including the sys.path cell pointing to your CLAM repo).

That’s it—OpenCV will import, and CLAM’s wsi_core modules will work.

🛠 Option B (stay in current kernel & repair versions)

If you can’t switch kernels and must keep using the current one, force consistent versions inside the notebook:

python
import sys, subprocess

    subprocess.check_call([sys.executable, "-m", "pip"] + list(args))

Then restart the kernel and try:

If you still see import errors after this, your user-site may still be mixing with system-site packages. In that case, Option A (venv) is the clean fix.

Why not “upgrade OpenCV to support NumPy 2”?

Newer OpenCV wheels (≥ 4.10) can support NumPy 2 on many platforms, but macOS arm64 sometimes still pulls a wheel built vs NumPy 1.x depending on PyPI metadata at install time. Pinning NumPy 1.26.4 + OpenCV 4.9.0.80 is the most reliable combo right now for your setup.

Great q. Short answer:

  • Yes, CLAM’s patcher can tile the whole slide (tissue areas) by default.

  • If you want ROI-only patches, you have two easy choices:

    1. Extract whole-slide patches first, then filter them to your ROI using your GeoJSON (fastest, no code changes).

    2. Use an ROI mask during patching so CLAM only tiles inside your ROI (one small code tweak or run a few lines in a notebook).

Here’s exactly how to do both.

A) Whole-slide patching (default; tiles tissue, not restricted to your ROI)

From the CLAM root:

bash
cd /Users/yhu10/Desktop/VLM/pipline_data_patch_level/ProstateCancer-main/CLAM
PYTHONPATH=. python create_patches_fp.py \
  --source /Users/yhu10/Desktop/VLM/pipline_data_patch_level/data/slides \
  --save_dir /Users/yhu10/Desktop/VLM/pipline_data_patch_level/data/patches \
  --patch_size 256 --step_size 256 \
  --seg --patch --stitch \
  --seg_level 0 --patch_level 0 \
  --preserve_coordinates

What you get:

  • .../data/patches/CMU-2.h5 with coords for every patch over tissue.

  • Stitched thumbnail and segmentation preview JPGs.

This is the simplest “make patches” command. It does not use your ROI; it tiles across all detected tissue.

B) ROI-only patches (recommended if you want to study that yellow tumor region)

Two ways:

B1. Post-filter (no code changes to CLAM)

  1. Run A to create CMU-2.h5.

  2. Use your GeoJSON (outer ring = ROI, inner ring = Tumor) to keep only patches inside the outer ring.

If you already have my filter script, run it. Minimal version:

python
# filter_patches_by_roi.py (mini)
from pathlib import Path
import h5py, json, numpy as np
from shapely.geometry import shape, Point

slide_id = "CMU-2"
h5_in  = Path("/Users/yhu10/Desktop/VLM/pipline_data_patch_level/data/patches")/f"{slide_id}.h5"
h5_out = Path("/Users/yhu10/Desktop/VLM/pipline_data_patch_level/data/patches")/f"{slide_id}_roi.h5"
gj     = Path("/Users/yhu10/Desktop/VLM/pipline_data_patch_level/path_level_projcet")/f"{slide_id}.geojson"

g = json.load(open(gj))
roi_polys = []
for f in g["features"]:
    cls = ((f.get("properties") or {}).get("classification") or "").lower()
    if "tumor" in cls: 
        continue  # skip inner tumor for the ROI filter; we keep everything inside outer ROI
    roi_polys.append(shape(f["geometry"]))

def in_roi(x,y):
    p = Point(float(x), float(y))
    return any(poly.contains(p) for poly in roi_polys)

with h5py.File(h5_in, "r") as fi, h5py.File(h5_out, "w") as fo:
    coords = fi["coords"][:]
    keep = np.array([i for i,(x,y) in enumerate(coords) if in_roi(x,y)], dtype=np.int64)
    # copy datasets, keeping only ROI indices when shapes match
    for k in fi.keys():
        if k == "coords": continue
        arr = fi[k][:]
        fo.create_dataset(k, data=(arr[keep] if getattr(arr, "shape", None) and len(arr)==len(coords) else arr))
    fo.create_dataset("coords", data=coords[keep])
print("ROI-only patches ->", h5_out)

Now use CMU-2_roi.h5 for downstream feature extraction / training. You can also generate tumor/benign pseudo-labels with the nested-ROI script I gave you earlier.

B2. Mask-guided patching (use your ROI during segmentation)

Your code has this hook already:

python
# in your create_patches notebook/functions:
def segment(WSI_object, seg_params=None, filter_params=None, mask_file=None):
    if mask_file is not None:
        WSI_object.initSegmentation(mask_file)   # <-- uses a provided mask
    else:
        WSI_object.segmentTissue(**seg_params, filter_params=filter_params)

So if you pass a mask_file, CLAM will segment using your mask.

Steps:

  1. Rasterize ROI GeoJSON → level-0 PNG mask (white inside ROI, black elsewhere). Use the script I gave (roi_to_mask.py). Output e.g.:

swift
/Users/yhu10/Desktop/VLM/pipline_data_patch_level/path_level_projcet/CMU-2_mask.png

  1. In a notebook, run patching with the mask:

python
import sys, pathlib
CLAM_ROOT = pathlib.Path("/Users/yhu10/Desktop/VLM/pipline_data_patch_level/ProstateCancer-main/CLAM")
sys.path.insert(0, str(CLAM_ROOT))

from wsi_core.wsi_utils import StitchCoords

This produces an H5 with patches only inside your ROI (because segmentation used your mask).

If your top-level seg_and_patch(...) doesn’t expose mask_file, just bypass it as above and call segment(..., mask_file=...) + patching(...) directly.

If you want ROI-only patches

You’ve got two easy choices:

A) Post-filter (simplest)

  1. Run the whole-slide patching above (produces CMU-2.h5).

  2. Filter to your ROI using your GeoJSON (outer ring = ROI). Run this Python one-liner:

bash
python - <<'PY'
from pathlib import Path
import h5py, json, numpy as np
from shapely.geometry import shape, Point

slide_id = "CMU-2"
h5_in  = Path("/Users/yhu10/Desktop/VLM/pipline_data_patch_level/data/patches")/f"{slide_id}.h5"
h5_out = Path("/Users/yhu10/Desktop/VLM/pipline_data_patch_level/data/patches")/f"{slide_id}_roi.h5"
gj     = Path("/Users/yhu10/Desktop/VLM/pipline_data_patch_level/path_level_projcet")/f"{slide_id}.geojson"

g = json.load(open(gj))
roi_polys = []
for f in g["features"]:
    cls = ((f.get("properties") or {}).get("classification") or "").lower()
    if "tumor" in cls:  # skip inner tumor; we want outer ROI
        continue
    roi_polys.append(shape(f["geometry"]))

def in_roi(x,y):
    p = Point(float(x), float(y))
    return any(poly.contains(p) for poly in roi_polys)

with h5py.File(h5_in, "r") as fi, h5py.File(h5_out, "w") as fo:
    coords = fi["coords"][:]
    keep = np.array([i for i,(x,y) in enumerate(coords) if in_roi(x,y)], dtype=np.int64)
    for k in fi.keys():
        if k == "coords": continue
        arr = fi[k][:]
        fo.create_dataset(k, data=(arr[keep] if getattr(arr, "shape", None) and len(arr)==len(coords) else arr))
    fo.create_dataset("coords", data=coords[keep])
print("ROI-only patches ->", h5_out)
PY

Now use CMU-2_roi.h5 downstream.

B) Mask-guided tiling (restrict during patching)

  1. Rasterize your outer ROI GeoJSON to a mask PNG at level-0 (white=ROI, black=background).

  2. Call CLAM’s segment(..., mask_file=...) then patching(...) (already supported in your code).
    If you want, I’ll paste a ready roi_to_mask.py + minimal notebook cell for this.

That error means your GeoJSON stores classification as a dict (e.g. {"name": "Tumor", ...}), not a plain string. Let’s make the parser robust to QuPath’s formats.

Replace your script with this hardened version

It handles classification as dict/string, falls back to other keys (name, class, pathClass, classificationName), and lowercases safely.

python
# /Users/yhu10/Desktop/VLM/pipline_data_patch_level/label_patches_from_nested_roi.py
from pathlib import Path
import h5py, json, pandas as pd
from shapely.geometry import shape, Point

slide_id = "CMU-2"

h5_path    = Path("/Users/yhu10/Desktop/VLM/pipline_data_patch_level/data/patches") / f"{slide_id}.h5"
geojson_fn = Path("/Users/yhu10/Desktop/VLM/pipline_data_patch_level/path_level_projcet") / f"{slide_id}.geojson"
out_csv    = Path("/Users/yhu10/Desktop/VLM/pipline_data_patch_level/data/labels") / f"{slide_id}_patch_labels.csv"

assert h5_path.exists(), f"patch h5 not found: {h5_path}"
assert geojson_fn.exists(), f"geojson not found: {geojson_fn}"
out_csv.parent.mkdir(parents=True, exist_ok=True)

def get_class_lower(props: dict) -> str:
    """
    Robustly extract a lowercase class name from various QuPath/GeoJSON schemas.
    """
    if not isinstance(props, dict):
        return ""
    cand = props.get("classification", None)
    # classification may be dict like {"name":"Tumor", ...}
    if isinstance(cand, dict):
        name = cand.get("name") or cand.get("displayName") or ""
        return str(name).lower()
    # or a raw string
    if isinstance(cand, str):
        return cand.lower()
    # fallbacks
    for k in ("name", "class", "pathClass", "classificationName", "Label"):
        v = props.get(k, "")
        if isinstance(v, dict):
            v = v.get("name", "")
        if isinstance(v, str) and v:
            return v.lower()
    return ""

# load polygons
g = json.load(open(geojson_fn))
tumor_polys, outer_polys = [], []
classes_seen = []

for feat in g.get("features", []):
    props = feat.get("properties") or {}
    cls = get_class_lower(props)
    classes_seen.append(cls or "<empty>")
    geom = shape(feat["geometry"])  # handles Polygon/MultiPolygon
    if "tumor" in cls:
        tumor_polys.append(geom)
    else:
        # treat any non-tumor annotation as outer ROI
        outer_polys.append(geom)

print("Found classes in GeoJSON:", sorted(set(classes_seen)))

def inside(polys, x, y):
    p = Point(float(x), float(y))
    # contains() excludes boundary; within/on edge handling:
    return any(poly.contains(p) or poly.touches(p) for poly in polys)

# label patches
rows = []
with h5py.File(h5_path, "r") as f:
    coords = f["coords"][:]  # (N,2) level-0 (x,y)

for i, (x, y) in enumerate(coords):
    if inside(tumor_polys, x, y):
        lab = "tumor"
    elif inside(outer_polys, x, y):
        lab = "benign"
    else:
        continue  # outside outer ROI → ignore
    rows.append({"slide_id": slide_id, "patch_id": i, "x": int(x), "y": int(y), "label": lab})

df = pd.DataFrame(rows)
df.to_csv(out_csv, index=False)
print("Saved:", out_csv)
print(df["label"].value_counts())

SLIDE_PATH = f"/Users/yhu10/Desktop/VLM/pipline_data_patch_level/data/slides/{SLIDE_ID}.svs"
LABEL_CSV = f"/Users/yhu10/Desktop/VLM/pipline_data_patch_level/data/labels/{SLIDE_ID}_patch_labels.csv"
OUT_DIR   = "/Users/yhu10/Desktop/VLM/pipline_data_patch_level/runs/patch_clf"
PATCH_SIZE = 256
BATCH_SIZE = 32
EPOCHS = 10  # 只有48个样本，10个epoch就够；如果你再标注多些再加
LR = 1e-4
VAL_SPLIT = 0.2
SEED = 42
# ------------------------------------------------------

os.makedirs(OUT_DIR, exist_ok=True)
random.seed(SEED); np.random.seed(SEED); torch.manual_seed(SEED)

class SlidePatchDataset(Dataset):
    def __init__(self, slide_path, df, aug=False):
        self.slide = openslide.OpenSlide(slide_path)
        self.df = df.reset_index(drop=True)
        self.aug = aug
        self.T = transforms.Compose([
            transforms.ToTensor(),
            transforms.Normalize(mean=[0.7,0.7,0.7], std=[0.2,0.2,0.2]),
        ])
        self.T_aug = transforms.Compose([
            transforms.ToTensor(),
            transforms.RandomHorizontalFlip(),
            transforms.RandomVerticalFlip(),
            transforms.RandomRotation(15),
            transforms.ColorJitter(0.1,0.1,0.1,0.05),
            transforms.Normalize(mean=[0.7,0.7,0.7], std=[0.2,0.2,0.2]),
        ])
        self.class_to_idx = {"benign":0, "tumor":1}

    def __len__(self):
        return len(self.df)

    def __getitem__(self, i):
        r = self.df.iloc[i]
        x, y = int(r.x), int(r.y)
        img = self.slide.read_region((x, y), 0, (PATCH_SIZE, PATCH_SIZE)).convert("RGB")
        img = self.T_aug(img) if self.aug else self.T(img)
        ylab = self.class_to_idx[r.label]
        return img, torch.tensor(ylab, dtype=torch.long)

def split_df(df, val_split=0.2):
    idx = np.arange(len(df))
    np.random.shuffle(idx)
    n_val = max(1, int(len(df)*val_split))
    val_idx = idx[:n_val]
    tr_idx  = idx[n_val:]
    return df.iloc[tr_idx].copy(), df.iloc[val_idx].copy()

def make_model():
    m = models.resnet18(weights=models.ResNet18_Weights.DEFAULT)
    m.fc = nn.Linear(m.fc.in_features, 2)
    return m

def main():
    df = pd.read_csv(LABEL_CSV)
    # 处理极度类不平衡：计算权重
    vc = df["label"].value_counts().to_dict()
    n_benign = vc.get("benign",0); n_tumor = vc.get("tumor",0)
    class_weights = torch.tensor([1.0, 1.0], dtype=torch.float32)
    if n_benign>0 and n_tumor>0:
        # 简单反比
        total = n_benign + n_tumor
        w_b = total/(2*n_benign); w_t = total/(2*n_tumor)
        class_weights = torch.tensor([w_b, w_t], dtype=torch.float32)
    print("class counts:", vc, "class_weights:", class_weights.tolist())

    train_df, val_df = split_df(df, VAL_SPLIT)
    train_ds = SlidePatchDataset(SLIDE_PATH, train_df, aug=True)
    val_ds   = SlidePatchDataset(SLIDE_PATH, val_df, aug=False)

    train_loader = DataLoader(train_ds, batch_size=BATCH_SIZE, shuffle=True, num_workers=0)
    val_loader   = DataLoader(val_ds, batch_size=BATCH_SIZE, shuffle=False, num_workers=0)

    device = torch.device("cuda" if torch.cuda.is_available() else "cpu")
    model = make_model().to(device)
    criterion = nn.CrossEntropyLoss(weight=class_weights.to(device))
    optimizer = optim.AdamW(model.parameters(), lr=LR)

    best_val = 0.0
    for epoch in range(1, EPOCHS+1):
        model.train()
        tr_loss = tr_correct = tr_total = 0
        for imgs, labs in train_loader:
            imgs, labs = imgs.to(device), labs.to(device)
            optimizer.zero_grad()
            logits = model(imgs)
            loss = criterion(logits, labs)
            loss.backward()
            optimizer.step()
            tr_loss += loss.item()*imgs.size(0)
            tr_correct += (logits.argmax(1)==labs).sum().item()
            tr_total += imgs.size(0)
        tr_acc = tr_correct / max(1,tr_total)

        model.eval()
        va_loss = va_correct = va_total = 0
        with torch.no_grad():
            for imgs, labs in val_loader:
                imgs, labs = imgs.to(device), labs.to(device)
                logits = model(imgs)
                loss = criterion(logits, labs)
                va_loss += loss.item()*imgs.size(0)
                va_correct += (logits.argmax(1)==labs).sum().item()
                va_total += imgs.size(0)
        va_acc = va_correct / max(1,va_total)
        print(f"Epoch {epoch:02d} | train_acc {tr_acc:.3f} | val_acc {va_acc:.3f}")

        if va_acc >= best_val:
            best_val = va_acc
            torch.save(model.state_dict(), f"{OUT_DIR}/resnet18_best.pt")
    # 也保存最后一版
    torch.save(model.state_dict(), f"{OUT_DIR}/resnet18_last.pt")
    with open(f"{OUT_DIR}/meta.json","w") as f:
        json.dump({"slide_id":SLIDE_ID,"patch_size":PATCH_SIZE,"counts":vc,"best_val_acc":best_val}, f, indent=2)

if __name__ == "__main__":
    main()

python
import json
from pathlib import Path
import numpy as np
import pandas as pd
from PIL import Image
import openslide
import h5py
import torch
import torch.nn as nn
from torchvision import models, transforms

SLIDE_ID = "CMU-2"
SLIDE_PATH = f"/Users/yhu10/Desktop/VLM/pipline_data_patch_level/data/slides/{SLIDE_ID}.svs"
H5_PATH    = f"/Users/yhu10/Desktop/VLM/pipline_data_patch_level/data/patches/{SLIDE_ID}.h5"
CKPT       = f"/Users/yhu10/Desktop/VLM/pipline_data_patch_level/runs/patch_clf/resnet18_best.pt"
OUT_CSV    = f"/Users/yhu10/Desktop/VLM/pipline_data_patch_level/runs/patch_clf/{SLIDE_ID}_pred.csv"
PATCH_SIZE = 256

device = torch.device("cuda" if torch.cuda.is_available() else "cpu")
T = transforms.Compose([
    transforms.ToTensor(),
    transforms.Normalize(mean=[0.7,0.7,0.7], std=[0.2,0.2,0.2]),
])

def load_model():
    m = models.resnet18(weights=None)
    m.fc = nn.Linear(m.fc.in_features, 2)
    m.load_state_dict(torch.load(CKPT, map_location=device))
    m.eval().to(device)
    return m

def main():
    slide = openslide.OpenSlide(SLIDE_PATH)
    with h5py.File(H5_PATH, "r") as f:
        coords = f["coords"][:]  # (N,2)

    model = load_model()
    probs = []
    bs = 64
    for i in range(0, len(coords), bs):
        batch = coords[i:i+bs]
        imgs = []
        for (x,y) in batch:
            img = slide.read_region((int(x),int(y)), 0, (PATCH_SIZE, PATCH_SIZE)).convert("RGB")
            imgs.append(T(img))
        imgs = torch.stack(imgs).to(device)
        with torch.no_grad():
            logits = model(imgs)
            p = torch.softmax(logits, dim=1)[:,1]  # prob of tumor class
        probs.extend(p.cpu().numpy().tolist())

    df = pd.DataFrame({"x": coords[:,0].astype(int), "y": coords[:,1].astype(int), "prob_tumor": probs})
    df.to_csv(OUT_CSV, index=False)

    # 简单的 slide-level 汇总（你可换其它规则）
    mean_prob = float(np.mean(probs))
    frac_high = float(np.mean((np.array(probs) >= 0.5)))
    slide_pred = "tumor" if mean_prob >= 0.5 else "benign"
    meta = {"slide_id": SLIDE_ID, "mean_prob": mean_prob, "frac_prob_ge_0.5": frac_high, "slide_pred": slide_pred}
    with open(Path(OUT_CSV).with_suffix(".json"), "w") as f:
        json.dump(meta, f, indent=2)
    print("Saved:", OUT_CSV)
    print("Slide-level:", meta)

if __name__ == "__main__":
    main()

What the 2nd script is doing

infer_slide_patch_probs.py loads your whole slide and the ~11.9k patch coordinates from CMU-2.h5, then:

  • reads each 256×256 patch via OpenSlide (CPU I/O),

  • runs the trained ResNet18,

  • writes a CSV of [x, y, prob_tumor] for every patch.

This can feel “quiet” because the script (as written) doesn’t print progress. It isn’t frozen; it’s just busy reading patches and running the model.

Quick fixes: add a progress bar (recommended)

You can stop it with Ctrl + C and run this progress-bar version instead (drop-in replacement):

  2. 粘贴并运行下面 Groovy 脚本（把 MEAS_NAME 改成你要看的测量名，这里是 prob_tumor）：

groovy
// 将检测点按测量值着色（仅用于显示，不改变分类）
def MEAS_NAME = 'prob_tumor'
def objs = getDetectionObjects()
for (def o : objs) {
    def v = o.getMeasurementList().getMeasurementValue(MEAS_NAME)
    if (Double.isNaN(v)) continue
    // 简单 0~1 映射到蓝→红，按需改
    def r = (int)Math.round(255 * Math.min(1, Math.max(0, v)))
    def b = 255 - r
    def color = new java.awt.Color(r, 0, b)
    o.setColor(color)
}

3) 按阈值把点分成“Tumor/Benign”，并设定颜色

菜单方式（如果你找得到“按测量阈值分类”的菜单）

  • 在对象列表里全选（或选中要处理的层级），然后找：
    Classify / Objects → Classify by measurement…（不同版本路径不同）
    选择 prob_tumor，设置阈值 0.5，≥0.5 设为 Tumor，否则 Benign。
    之后在 Edit → Preferences → Path classes 里可自定义两类的颜色（例如 Tumor=红，Benign=绿）。

脚本方式（最稳，一键完成）

  1. 打开 Automate → Show script editor

  2. 粘贴运行：

groovy
// 按 prob_tumor 阈值将检测点设置为 Tumor / Benign，并设置类颜色
def TH = 0.5
def MEAS = 'prob_tumor'

// 确保类存在并设颜色（可改RGB）
import qupath.lib.objects.classes.PathClassFactory
def tumorClass  = PathClassFactory.getPathClass('Tumor',  255, 0, 0)     // 红
def benignClass = PathClassFactory.getPathClass('Benign', 0, 200, 0)     // 绿

def nTumor = 0, nBenign = 0
for (def o : getDetectionObjects()) {
    def v = o.getMeasurementList().getMeasurementValue(MEAS)
    if (Double.isNaN(v)) continue
    if (v >= TH) { o.setPathClass(tumorClass);  nTumor++  }
    else         { o.setPathClass(benignClass); nBenign++ }
}
print "Set classes by threshold ${TH} on ${MEAS}: Tumor=${nTumor}, Benign=${nBenign}"
fireHierarchyUpdate()

这样做完，你就可以用 Class color 来显示两类颜色；也能在 Measurements 里保留原始 prob_tumor 数值。

import qupath.lib.color.ColorTools

def MEAS_NAME = 'prob_tumor'   // 你要显示的测量名
def objs = getDetectionObjects()

for (def o : objs) {
    def v = o.getMeasurementList().getMeasurementValue(MEAS_NAME)

    int g = 0
    int b = (int)Math.round(255 * (1 - v))
    // 在 0.6.x 用 setColorRGB & ColorTools
    o.setColorRGB(ColorTools.packRGB(r, g, b))
}

        def prop = o.getProperties()?.get(MEAS)
        if (prop instanceof Number) v = prop as double
    }
    if (Double.isNaN(v)) continue

    if (v >= TH) { o.setPathClass(tumorClass);  nT++ }
    else         { o.setPathClass(benignClass); nB++ }
}
fireHierarchyUpdate()
print "Classified by ${MEAS}@${TH}: Tumor=${nT}, Benign=${nB}"

你碰到的报错是：

  • PathClassFactory 在 0.4+ 被标记为过时；0.6 要用 PathClass.fromString；

  • setColorRGB 在 PathClass 上不可用，应该用 setColor(r,g,b)；

  • getMeasurementValue(String) 在 0.6 的 DefaultMeasurementList 上有时不可用，但 getMeasurementValueByName(String) 可以；我加了对 properties 的回退读取，避免导入差异导致脚本失败。

groovy
// 把属性中的 prob_tumor 复制到 Measurements，兼容 0.6 API
String KEY = 'prob_tumor'
int n = 0
for (def o : getAnnotationObjects()) {  // 你的点是 Annotation
    def props = o.getProperties()
    if (props == null || !props.containsKey(KEY)) continue
    def v = props.get(KEY)
    if (!(v instanceof Number)) continue
    def ml = o.getMeasurementList()
    if (ml == null) continue
    // 0.6 常用：按名写入测量
    ml.putMeasurement(KEY, (v as Number).doubleValue())
    n++
}
fireHierarchyUpdate()
print "Wrote ${KEY} into Measurements for ${n} annotations."

请在你的 (pathlvl) 环境里运行下面的 Python，把 CMU-2_pred.csv 转成合规的 GeoJSON：

bash
python - <<'PY'
import pandas as pd, json
from pathlib import Path

slide_id = "CMU-2"
csv = Path("/Users/yhu10/Desktop/VLM/pipline_data_patch_level/runs/patch_clf")/f"{slide_id}_pred.csv"

    features.append({
        "type": "Feature",

        "properties": {
            "classification": {"name": "Prediction"},   # 可选
            "measurements": {"prob_tumor": float(r.prob_tumor)}
        }
    })
geo = {"type": "FeatureCollection", "features": features}

ChatGPT said:

这个报错是因为我们生成的 GeoJSON 结构不符合 QuPath 0.6 的期望。
在 0.6 里，properties.measurements 需要是数组（[{"name": "...","value": ...}]），而不是字典 { "prob_tumor": 0.73 }。结构不匹配时，QuPath 的解析器会在读取 classification / pathClass 时抛出你看到的错误。

直接把你的脚本改成下面这个 QuPath-兼容版本（测量是数组；附带可选的 classification、isLocked）：

python
import json, pandas as pd
from pathlib import Path

SLIDE_ID = "CMU-2"
PRED_CSV = f"/Users/yhu10/Desktop/VLM/pipline_data_patch_level/runs/patch_clf/{SLIDE_ID}_pred.csv"
OUT_GEO  = f"/Users/yhu10/Desktop/VLM/pipline_data_patch_level/runs/patch_clf/{SLIDE_ID}_pred_qpath.geojson"

df = pd.read_csv(PRED_CSV)   # 需要列: x, y, prob_tumor

features = []
for r in df.itertuples():
    features.append({
        "type": "Feature",
        "id": f"patch_{r.Index}",
        "geometry": {
            "type": "Point",
            "coordinates": [float(r.x), float(r.y)]
        },
        "properties": {
            # 可选：给这些点一个类别名（QuPath 会当作 PathClass）
            "classification": {"name": "Prediction"},
            "isLocked": False,
            # 关键：QuPath 0.6 期望 measurements 是数组，而不是字典
            "measurements": [
                {"name": "prob_tumor", "value": float(r.prob_tumor)}
            ]
        }
    })

geo = {"type": "FeatureCollection", "features": features}
Path(OUT_GEO).parent.mkdir(parents=True, exist_ok=True)
with open(OUT_GEO, "w") as f:
    json.dump(geo, f)
print("Saved:", OUT_GEO)

导入步骤

  1. 在 QuPath 里先把旧的那些点全选删除（避免叠加）。

  2. File → Import objects from file… 选择新的：
    .../runs/patch_clf/CMU-2_pred_qpath.geojson

  3. 选中任意一点，底部 Measurements 面板里应该能看到 prob_tumor。

  4. 画热图：Analyze → Measurement maps… → Object type 选 Annotations → Measurement 选 prob_tumor（Min=0, Max=1）。

  5. 或者：Classify → Classify by measurement… → 选 prob_tumor，阈值 0.5（可自定义），得到 Tumor/Benign 两类上色。

没关系，GeoJSON 在 QuPath 0.6.0 的解析比较挑，你现在最快的办法是绕过 GeoJSON：直接在 QuPath 里从 CSV 读入点并把 prob_tumor 写进 Measurements。这样 100% 可用，而且不依赖 GeoJSON 的格式。

下面给你一段 适配 QuPath 0.6.0 的 Groovy 脚本，一步完成：读取你给的
/Users/yhu10/Desktop/VLM/pipline_data_patch_level/runs/patch_clf/CMU-2_pred.csv，为每行 (x,y,prob_tumor) 创建一个点对象，并把 prob_tumor 作为测量值写进去。

你只需在 QuPath 里打开该切片 → Automate → Show script editor → 粘贴运行即可。

groovy
// === QuPath 0.6.0：从 CSV 导入点，并写入 prob_tumor 测量 ===
// CSV 需要三列：x, y, prob_tumor（与你的 CMU-2_pred.csv 一致）
// 每一行会创建一个点 Annotation，并在 Measurements 写入 prob_tumor

import qupath.lib.objects.PathObjects
import qupath.lib.roi.ROIs
import qupath.lib.gui.dialogs.Dialogs

// ---- 修改成你的 CSV 路径 ----
def csvPath = '/Users/yhu10/Desktop/VLM/pipline_data_patch_level/runs/patch_clf/CMU-2_pred.csv'

// 是否先删除已有的小点（避免重复导入）
boolean removeExisting = true

// ----------------------------------------------------------------

def imageData = getCurrentImageData()
if (imageData == null) {
    Dialogs.showErrorMessage('Import CSV', 'Open a slide first.')
    return
}

// 可选：删除已有 Annotation 点
if (removeExisting) {
    def anns = getAnnotationObjects()
    if (!anns.isEmpty()) {
        removeObjects(anns, true)
        print "Removed ${anns.size()} existing annotations."
    }
}

// 读取 CSV
def file = new File(csvPath)
assert file.exists() : "CSV not found: " + csvPath

def header = null
def toAdd = []
int n = 0

file.withReader('UTF-8') { br ->
    br.eachLine { line, lineNo ->
        if (lineNo == 1) {
            header = line.split(',').collect { it.trim() }
            return
        }
        if (line.trim().isEmpty()) return
        def parts = line.split(',')
        if (parts.size() < 3) return

        // 取列索引（根据表头名寻找）
        def ix = header.indexOf('x')
        def iy = header.indexOf('y')
        def ip = header.indexOf('prob_tumor')
        if (ix < 0 || iy < 0 || ip < 0) {
            throw new RuntimeException("CSV must contain columns: x, y, prob_tumor")
        }

        double x = parts[ix].trim() as double
        double y = parts[iy].trim() as double
        double p = parts[ip].trim() as double

        // 创建一个点 ROI（位于 level 0 像素坐标）
        def roi = ROIs.createPointsROI(x, y)
        def ann = PathObjects.createAnnotationObject(roi, null) // 不先设类别

        // 写入测量值
        def ml = ann.getMeasurementList()
        ml.putMeasurement('prob_tumor', p)

        toAdd << ann
        n++
    }
}

addObjects(toAdd)
fireHierarchyUpdate()
print "Imported ${n} points from CSV with 'prob_tumor' as measurement."

导入后怎么做热图 / 分类

A) 画概率热图（不用脚本；最稳）

  • 菜单 Analyze → Measurement maps…（或 Show/ Create measurement maps…）

  • Object type 选 Annotations（我们刚创建的就是 Annotation 点）

  • Measurement 选 prob_tumor

  • Min=0, Max=1，配色选 Fire/Turbo；想更连续就把 Radius/Blur 调大

  • 应用即可看到“概率越高颜色越热”的效果

B) 按阈值分 Tumor / Benign（不用脚本也行）

  • Classify → Classify by measurement…

  • Object type: Annotations

  • Measurement: prob_tumor

  • 阈值 0.5（或你自定义），≥ 阈值设为 Tumor，否则 Benign

  • 若要自定义颜色：Edit → Preferences → Path classes 里把 Tumor 设红、Benign 设绿

想用脚本着色/分类（0.6 兼容版）

渐变着色（蓝→红）

groovy
import qupath.lib.common.ColorTools
def MEAS = 'prob_tumor'
int n=0
for (def o : getAnnotationObjects()) {
    def ml = o.getMeasurementList(); if (ml == null) continue
    double v = ml.getMeasurementValueByName(MEAS); if (Double.isNaN(v)) continue
    v = Math.max(0, Math.min(1, v))
    int r=(int)Math.round(255*v), g=0, b=(int)Math.round(255*(1-v))
    o.setColorRGB(ColorTools.packRGB(r,g,b)); n++
}
fireHierarchyUpdate(); print "Colored "+n+" by "+MEAS

阈值分类（Tumor/Benign）

groovy
import qupath.lib.objects.classes.PathClass
double TH=0.5; String MEAS='prob_tumor'
def tumor=PathClass.fromString('Tumor'); tumor.setColor(255,0,0)
def benign=PathClass.fromString('Benign'); benign.setColor(0,200,0)
int nT=0,nB=0
for (def o : getAnnotationObjects()) {
  def ml=o.getMeasurementList(); if (ml==null) continue
  double v=ml.getMeasurementValueByName(MEAS); if (Double.isNaN(v)) continue
  if (v>=TH){o.setPathClass(tumor); nT++} else {o.setPathClass(benign); nB++}
}
fireHierarchyUpdate(); print "Classified: Tumor="+nT+", Benign="+nB

  • 用 CSV→脚本导入 方式完全避开这些差异，最稳、最好调试。
